  "doc_id": "19093",
  "text": "For wave packets the expectation value cα is the group velocity v gp and the space displacement in a time lapse ∆t generated by H D corresponds to the classical v gp ∆t. On the other hand T acts on the continous momentum space, generating a change of momentum ∆p = mv gp = m 0 γv gp , where γ = [1 − (v/c) 2 ] −1 is the Lorentz factor, and consequently an energy change from E(p) to E(p + mv gp ) in both branches of the relativistic energy spectrum. This circumvents Pauli's correct objection that a commutation relation [T, H] = i where T acts on the energy spectrum, necessarily implies a continuum energy spectrum from −∞ to +∞ , contradicting the fact that the energy expectation value is expected to be positive and that there also may be discrete eigenvalues [CITATION_1] .",
